                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Manchuria/1–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 1, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Dept appreciates your reports on Manchurian developments (Urtel 136 Jan 20
                    11 a.m. and previous) and desires that you continue to maintain contact with
                    Sino authorities with view to keeping us currently informed on matters of
                    significance occurring in that area.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
